==Old English==

===Etymology===
From [[and]] ‘against, off’ + [[wlitan|wlītan]] ‘to look, behold’.  Cognate with Old Norse [[andlit]] (Swedish [[anlete]]), Old High German [[antlizzi]] (German [[Antlitz]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'andwlɪta/}}

===Noun===
'''andwlita''' {{m}} ({{p}} '''andwlitan''')
# [[form]], [[face]]

===Descendants===
Middle English [[anleth]].

